      • checkSeverity

        public boolean checkSeverity(Problem.Severity minimumLevel)
        Checks whether a given list of problems contains at least one problem with the specified or a greater severity level.
        Parameters:
        minimumLevel - The minimum severity level (one of Problem.Severity.INFO, Problem.Severity.WARNING, or Problem.Severity.ERROR).
        Returns:
        true if the list contains a problem with severity at the given minimum level or above, false otherwise.
